37. The MSS. of the De Officiis are very numerous. They have all come from a common source, but may be divided into two classes; at the head of one stand the Beruensis e, of the 13th century, and the Palat. p; of the other family the best are a MS. at Barnberg, one at VViirzburg, the MS. b at Berne, all dating from the tenth century.
